[I] A network authentication protocol

[T] Kerberos is a network authentication protocol. It is designed to
[T] provide strong authentication for client/server applications by
[T] using secret-key cryptography.

[U] https://web.mit.edu/kerberos/dist/index.html

[A] MIT
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/security
[F] CROSS

[L] MIT
